50|$|In 1951, Sammet took a {{position}} at the Metropolitan Life Insurance Company as a trainee actuary. She {{agreed to participate in}} an in-house training program to learn about punched card <b>accounting</b> <b>machines.</b> Sammet took to the electronic <b>accounting</b> <b>machines,</b> but was unable to work with the machines after her training was complete. She left her position at the insurance office and enrolled at Columbia University to pursue a Ph.D. in mathematics. Sammet worked as a teaching assistant at Barnard College during the 1952-1953 school year before she decided that the academic life was not for her.|$|E
